  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then comes the next miracle-- oh, no.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the meantime, we had a note from my father.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We found out that he's in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he chose to come to Auschwitz because he knew that our area was emptied out and taken to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he wanted to come to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the note said, don't worry, we'll be-- this will be over, and we'll be soon together.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I think he was dead within two, three weeks after that, because we understand that he died in August.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was gassed, because he had-- he became edemic in the legs, which meant that he couldn't walk very easily, and so he was gassed.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So-- but we didn't know that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We didn't know that he died then.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were quite sure that he's alive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Having recieved--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, not until-- literally, not until the end of the war, because although we heard some stories, but you don't believe it, no, until-- until it actually is proven by absence.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My idea was, right through, we've got to get out of here.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, it is true that to get out of Auschwitz was a huge gamble, because you didn't know whether you were getting out of Auschwitz or whether you were taken straight into the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I figured that to stay there is certain death, because you can only survive that long by luck.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Luck runs out.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Plus time was passing, and the Russians were-- we knew that the Russian front is slowly coming nearer, and we knew that we must be in the way of the Russians, so the Russians were-- and my idea was, and I wasn't far out, that when the Russians come, they'll kill everyone.",
      "word_count": 52
    }
  ],
